   "source": [
    "{\n",
    " \"cells\": [\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"id\": \"m001\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"# Fraud Pattern Analysis\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"## Project Overview\\n\",\n",
    "    \"This notebook analyzes transaction data to identify patterns, spikes, segments, and transaction characteristics associated with fraudulent activity.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"## Learning Objectives\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Explore transaction-level data for fraud indicators.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Identify temporal, amount-based, and category-based fraud patterns.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Compare fraudulent vs legitimate transaction profiles.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Understand imbalanced class analysis challenges.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"## Business / Research Problem\\n\",\n",
    "    \"Fraud costs financial institutions billions annually. Understanding fraud patterns enables better detection rules and model features.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"## Why This Analysis Matters\\n\",\n",
    "    \"Rule-based fraud detection catches known patterns. EDA uncovers new patterns that can be codified into rules or model features.\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"id\": \"m002\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Dataset Overview\\n\",\n",
    "    \"Synthetic dataset of **10,000 transactions** with ~3% fraud rate.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"## Dataset Source and License Notes\\n\",\n",
    "    \"Synthetically generated for educational purposes.\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"id\": \"c001\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"import subprocess, sys, importlib\\n\",\n",
    "    \"for pkg in [\\\"pandas\\\", \\\"numpy\\\", \\\"matplotlib\\\", \\\"seaborn\\\", \\\"scipy\\\"]:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    try:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        importlib.import_module(pkg)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    except ImportError:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        subprocess.check_call([sys.executable, \\\"-m\\\", \\\"pip\\\", \\\"install\\\", \\\"-q\\\", pkg])\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(\\\"Environment ready.\\\")\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"id\": \"c002\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"import numpy as np\\n\",\n",
    "    \"import pandas as pd\\n\",\n",
    "    \"import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\\n\",\n",
    "    \"import seaborn as sns\\n\",\n",
    "    \"from scipy import stats\\n\",\n",
    "    \"import warnings\\n\",\n",
    "    \"warnings.filterwarnings(\\\"ignore\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"sns.set_style(\\\"whitegrid\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"%matplotlib inline\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"id\": \"c003\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"SEED = 42\\n\",\n",
    "    \"N = 10000\\n\",\n",
    "    \"CATEGORIES = [\\\"Online Purchase\\\", \\\"ATM Withdrawal\\\", \\\"POS Terminal\\\", \\\"Wire Transfer\\\", \\\"Mobile Payment\\\"]\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(\\\"Configuration loaded.\\\")\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"id\": \"c004\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"rng = np.random.default_rng(SEED)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"dates = pd.date_range(\\\"2025-01-01\\\", \\\"2025-12-31\\\", freq=\\\"h\\\")[:N*2]\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"rows = []\\n\",\n",
    "    \"for i in range(N):\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    is_fraud = int(rng.random() < 0.03)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    category = rng.choice(CATEGORIES, p=[0.35,0.15,0.25,0.10,0.15])\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    if is_fraud:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        # Fraud tends to be higher amount, odd hours, online\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        amount = max(10, round(rng.exponential(800), 2))\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        hour = int(rng.choice([0,1,2,3,4,22,23,12,15]))\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        category = rng.choice([\\\"Online Purchase\\\", \\\"Wire Transfer\\\", \\\"ATM Withdrawal\\\"], p=[0.5,0.3,0.2])\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    else:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        amount = max(1, round(rng.exponential(80), 2))\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        hour = int(rng.choice(range(6,23)))\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    \\n\",\n",
    "    \"    date = rng.choice(dates)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    rows.append({\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        \\\"txn_id\\\": f\\\"TXN{i+1:06d}\\\", \\\"date\\\": date, \\\"hour\\\": hour,\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        \\\"amount\\\": amount, \\\"category\\\": category,\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        \\\"is_fraud\\\": is_fraud,\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    })\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"df = pd.DataFrame(rows)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"df[\\\"date\\\"] = pd.to_datetime(df[\\\"date\\\"])\\n\",\n",
    "    \"df[\\\"day_of_week\\\"] = df[\\\"date\\\"].dt.day_name()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f\\\"Dataset: {df.shape}, Fraud rate: {df['is_fraud'].mean():.2%}\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"df.head()\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"id\": \"c005\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"print(f\\\"Missing: {df.isnull().sum().sum()}\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f\\\"Fraud txns: {df['is_fraud'].sum()}, Legit: {(~df['is_fraud'].astype(bool)).sum()}\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(\\\"✅ Validation passed.\\\")\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"id\": \"c006\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"fig, axes = plt.subplots(2, 2, figsize=(14, 10))\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"# Amount distribution\\n\",\n",
    "    \"for label, color in [(0, \\\"#2ecc71\\\"), (1, \\\"#e74c3c\\\")]:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    subset = df[df[\\\"is_fraud\\\"]==label]\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    axes[0,0].hist(subset[\\\"amount\\\"].clip(0,2000), bins=50, alpha=0.5, label=\\\"Fraud\\\" if label else \\\"Legit\\\", color=color)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"axes[0,0].set_title(\\\"Transaction Amount Distribution\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"axes[0,0].legend()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"# Fraud rate by category\\n\",\n",
    "    \"df.groupby(\\\"category\\\")[\\\"is_fraud\\\"].mean().sort_values().plot(kind=\\\"barh\\\", ax=axes[0,1], color=\\\"coral\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"axes[0,1].set_title(\\\"Fraud Rate by Category\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"# Fraud by hour\\n\",\n",
    "    \"hour_fraud = df.groupby(\\\"hour\\\")[\\\"is_fraud\\\"].mean()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"axes[1,0].bar(hour_fraud.index, hour_fraud.values, color=\\\"steelblue\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"axes[1,0].set_title(\\\"Fraud Rate by Hour\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"axes[1,0].set_xlabel(\\\"Hour\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"# Amount comparison\\n\",\n",
    "    \"sns.boxplot(data=df, x=\\\"is_fraud\\\", y=\\\"amount\\\", ax=axes[1,1], palette=[\\\"#2ecc71\\\",\\\"#e74c3c\\\"])\\n\",\n",
    "    \"axes[1,1].set_title(\\\"Amount: Fraud vs Legit\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"axes[1,1].set_ylim(0, df[\\\"amount\\\"].quantile(0.95))\\n\",\n",
    "    \"axes[1,1].set_xticklabels([\\\"Legitimate\\\", \\\"Fraud\\\"])\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"plt.tight_layout()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"plt.show()\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"id\": \"c007\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"# Statistical comparison\\n\",\n",
    "    \"fraud_amounts = df[df[\\\"is_fraud\\\"]==1][\\\"amount\\\"]\\n\",\n",
    "    \"legit_amounts = df[df[\\\"is_fraud\\\"]==0][\\\"amount\\\"]\\n\",\n",
    "    \"stat, p = stats.mannwhitneyu(fraud_amounts, legit_amounts, alternative=\\\"greater\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f\\\"Fraud avg amount: ${fraud_amounts.mean():.2f}\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f\\\"Legit avg amount: ${legit_amounts.mean():.2f}\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f\\\"Mann-Whitney U: p={p:.2e} → {'Significant' if p<0.05 else 'Not significant'}\\\")\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"id\": \"m003\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Key Findings\\n\",\n",
    "    \"1. **Fraudulent transactions have significantly higher average amounts** than legitimate ones.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"2. **Late-night and early-morning hours show higher fraud rates.**\\n\",\n",
    "    \"3. **Online purchases and wire transfers have the highest fraud rates** by category.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"4. **The extreme class imbalance (3% fraud) must be addressed** in any modeling approach.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"## Limitations\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Synthetic data; real fraud is much more sophisticated.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- No velocity features (transactions per hour per card).\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- No geographic or device data.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"## Recommendations / Next Steps\\n\",\n",
    "    \"1. Flag high-amount online transactions during off-hours for review.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"2. Build velocity-based features (transactions per time window).\\n\",\n",
    "    \"3. Use anomaly detection models designed for imbalanced data.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"4. Monitor fraud rate trends by category monthly.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"## Common Mistakes\\n\",\n",
    "    \"1. Using accuracy to evaluate fraud models (misleading with 97% non-fraud).\\n\",\n",
    "    \"2. Not considering the cost of false positives (blocking legitimate transactions).\\n\",\n",
    "    \"3. Over-fitting to known fraud patterns while missing novel ones.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"4. Not updating rules as fraud patterns evolve.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"## Mini Challenge / Exercises\\n\",\n",
    "    \"1. Create an anomaly score based on amount, hour, and category.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"2. Build an isolation forest model and evaluate with PR-AUC.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"3. Calculate the financial impact of undetected fraud.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"4. Design a rule-based alert system with configurable thresholds.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"## Final Summary / Key Takeaways\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- **Amount, timing, and channel are the strongest fraud signals.**\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- **Fraud analysis must account for severe class imbalance.**\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- **EDA is essential before building detection models** to understand feature behavior.\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  }\n",
    " ],\n",
